      "side": 1,
      "message": "In addition to frame 0, there are a few cases where a frame can be independent and not fill the frame:\n- the prior frame\u0027s DisposalMethod is kRestoreBGColor and it is independent [1]\n- all prior frames are DisposalMethod::kRestorePrevious [2]\n- the frame rect covers the frame rect of all prior frames (back through an independent frame) [3]\n- there\u0027s a fourth place where we can mark a frame independent [4], but I don\u0027t think we\u0027ll ever reach that point. That ought to get caught by [1]\n\n\n[1] https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/05ff93c43ea57fd62cd1bc36ab7cd9b6112a7ecf/src/codec/SkCodec.cpp#773\n[2] https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/05ff93c43ea57fd62cd1bc36ab7cd9b6112a7ecf/src/codec/SkCodec.cpp#760\n[3] https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/05ff93c43ea57fd62cd1bc36ab7cd9b6112a7ecf/src/codec/SkCodec.cpp#791\n[4] https://skia.googlesource.com/skia/+/05ff93c43ea57fd62cd1bc36ab7cd9b6112a7ecf/src/codec/SkCodec.cpp#803",
